cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a method and algorithm for autonomous detection of new classes and learning from extremely weak supervision. This involves sub-selecting features based on accumulated data density per feature per class, which suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions testing on two challenging datasets, which indicates a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL) as potential sub-categories. Finally, the use of autonomously self-learning models suggests a focus on neural networks (cs.NE).
